# CONVENTIONS — [APP_NAME]

Mandatory conventions for all **new** code in this project. The goal: anything
new is born identical in shape to the established mold, so the codebase stays
consistent across domains and contributors.

> **What this file is — and what it is NOT.**
> CONVENTIONS is the **prescriptive *how*** — standing rules you consult
> **before** writing code. Distinguish it from its neighbours:
> - `documentation/decisions.md` — the ***why / when*** of a choice (durable
>   ADRs + firm premises; point-in-time, supersedable). A convention often
>   *derives* from a decision (ADR "schema-per-domain" → the schema convention
>   below).
> - `documentation/knowledge/anti-decisions.md` — approaches the team **tried
>   and abandoned**, with evidence.
>
> Keep this file short and prescriptive. When a convention changes, edit it here
> **and** record the rationale as an ADR in `decisions.md`.

